{
  "texts": [
    "• The subject's perspective description of a window 𝑤 𝑡 has the following structure:-First, it reports the location where the subject is at the beginning of the window (if this information can be inferred from sensor data).",
    "-Then, it reports the Already active states (e.g., \"the subject is already sitting on the couch\").",
    "-Finally, for each room visited by the subject during 𝑤 𝑡 (in chronological order), the description includes the actions (derived by the states) performed by the subject during 𝑤 𝑡 generated leveraging the Inner and Persistent states.",
    "• To transform each state into actions described in natural language, we implemented simple rules leveraging its category, its property 𝜎, its relative temporal order with the other states in 𝑤 𝑡, its duration, and the semantic location of the corresponding sensor.",
    "Hence, Window2Text assumes the availability of meta-data describing how to map each sensor 𝑆 to its location in the home and the corresponding 𝜎."
  ]
}